The Chilean Safety Association (Spanish: Asociaci√≥n Chilena de Seguridad, also known as ACHS) is a Chilean private non-profit organization, focused in development of risk prevention programs, and occupational accidents coverage.
ACHS was created on November 13, 1957, after Ladislao Lira presented a project to the Directory of Sociedad de Fomento Fabril. The current president of the Chilean Safety Association is Eugenio Heiremeans Despouy.
